## OpenClaw Channel Plugin Architecture Analysis

I've thoroughly explored the IRC, Telegram, and Nostr channel plugins in the OpenClaw codebase. Here's a comprehensive breakdown of the plugin structure:

### **1. Directory Structure**

All three plugins are located in `/extensions/` and follow the same organizational pattern:

**IRC Plugin:**
```
extensions/irc/
├── openclaw.plugin.json      (manifest)
├── package.json              (npm config with plugin metadata)
├── index.ts                  (main entry point)
├── setup-entry.ts            (setup wizard entry)
├── api.ts                    (public API barrel)
├── channel-config-api.ts     (channel config API)
├── src/
│   ├── channel.ts            (main ChannelPlugin registration)
│   ├── runtime.ts            (runtime store)
│   ├── runtime-api.ts        (runtime API barrel)
│   ├── accounts.ts           (account resolution)
│   ├── types.ts              (type definitions)
│   ├── config-schema.ts      (Zod validation schema)
│   ├── setup-core.ts         (setup logic)
│   ├── setup-surface.ts      (UI wizard)
│   ├── inbound.ts            (message ingestion)
│   ├── send.ts               (message delivery)
│   ├── monitor.ts            (connection monitoring)
│   ├── probe.ts              (connectivity testing)
│   ├── policy.ts             (DM/group policies)
│   ├── normalize.ts          (target normalization)
│   └── ... other modules
```

**Telegram Plugin** - More complex (~90 TypeScript files):
```
extensions/telegram/
├── openclaw.plugin.json
├── package.json              (includes dependencies: grammy, @grammyjs/runner)
├── index.ts
├── setup-entry.ts
├── api.ts
├── runtime-api.ts
├── channel-config-api.ts
├── allow-from.ts
├── session-key-api.ts
├── src/
│   ├── channel.ts            (main plugin registration)
│   ├── channel.setup.ts      (setup variant)
│   ├── runtime.ts
│   ├── accounts.ts
│   ├── config-schema.ts
│   ├── bot/                  (bot-specific logic)
│   │   ├── types.ts
│   │   ├── helpers.ts
│   │   ├── delivery.ts
│   │   └── ...
│   ├── thread-bindings.ts
│   ├── exec-approvals.ts
│   ├── monitor.ts
│   ├── send.ts
│   └── ... many more modules
```

**Nostr Plugin:**
```
extensions/nostr/
├── openclaw.plugin.json
