## 5. Boundary Conventions (from AGENTS.md files)

### Plugin SDK (`src/plugin-sdk/AGENTS.md`):
- **Public contracts:** docs in `docs/plugins/*`, type definitions in `plugin-entry.ts`, `core.ts`
- **Rules:**
  - Use narrow, purpose-built subpaths (not broad re-exports)
  - Avoid exposing internal convenience from `src/channels/**`, `src/agents/**`, `src/plugins/**`
  - Prefer `api.runtime` over direct internal imports
  - When adding public seams, align: docs, `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json`, `entrypoints.ts`, `package.json` exports

### Channels (`src/channels/AGENTS.md`):
- **Public contracts:** types in `types.plugin.ts`, `types.core.ts`, `types.adapters.ts`
- **Rules:**
  - Route extension-facing surfaces through `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*`
  - When bundled/third-party channels need new seams, add SDK contracts first
  - Shared channel changes affect all channels — test routing, pairing, allowlists, reply behavior

